This article is a presidential proclamation issued by President Barack Obama on September 10, 2015, declaring September 11 through September 13 as National Days of Prayer and Remembrance. The proclamation reflects on the events of September 11, 2001, and pays tribute to the nearly 3,000 lives lost and the first responders who sacrificed their lives. It emphasizes the unity and resilience of the American people in the aftermath of the attacks and calls for continued remembrance and prayer. The proclamation also invites people around the world to participate in the commemoration.